            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\",\"id\":\"msg_01ByKP2w4YoX2YdxdPha3Bax\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The current IndexPage.tsx file looks correct and doesn't have the errors mentioned. However, based on the error message provided, it seems like the issue was:\\n\\n1. **Line 5 had `<NonExistentComponent />`** - a component that doesn't exist\\n2. **Missing closing tag** - The return statement had `<NonExistentComponent />` followed by a `<div>` without proper JSX structure (two adjacent elements without a parent wrapper)\\n\\nThe error \\\"Expected ',', got 'ident'\\\" typically occurs when there are syntax errors in JSX, like having two adjacent elements without a fragment or parent wrapper.\\n\\nLooking at the current file, it appears to already be fixed. But let me verify the build works by checking if there are any other potential issues in the codebase:\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01AgJdemHh9tjp4iRbntXGyH\",\"name\":\"read_file\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/src/main.tsx\",\"offset\":0,\"limit\":50}},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01BVbek9ZGvN6UtcV11jL2LY\",\"name\":\"ls\",\"input\":{\"path\":\"/src/components\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":7,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":663,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":8395,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":663,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":307,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
